New Records: Australia's total of 3-215 is their third-best T20 chase.
Marsh’s side became the first nation to concede more than 200 in four consecutive T20 internationals.
Key Match Events: Tim David struck a boundary off the final ball to secure a six-wicket win for Australia.
Captain Mitch Marsh scored 72 off 44 balls.
Rachin Ravindra hit six sixes in his 68 off 35 balls.
Adam Zampa and Glenn Maxwell were ineffective, with Zampa conceding 42 runs off three overs and Maxwell 32 off two.
Post-Match Reflections: Doubts linger over whether Steve Smith will go to his fourth T20 World Cup, with this series being Australia’s last hitout before the June tournament.
